:::summary
The Sermon on the Mount (Matthew 5–7) is the greatest single discourse in human history — the extended teaching in which Jesus Christ laid out the ethics, the spirituality, and the vision of the Kingdom of God that define Christian discipleship. Delivered on a hillside in Galilee, this sermon contains the Beatitudes, the Lord's Prayer, and some of the most demanding and most beautiful moral teaching ever recorded, calling those who hear it not merely to outward compliance with law but to an inward transformation of the heart.
:::

